2014;;Ramanujan;;British;;Director: Gnana Rajasekaran;;Director: Gnana RajasekaranCast: Abhinay Vaddi, Abbas, Suhasini Maniratnam, Kevin McGowan, Bhama, Michael Lieber;;unknown;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ramanujan_(film);;Set in the early 1900s, the film traces the life of the prodigious math genius Srinivasa Ramanujan from the time he was a young Tamil Brahmin to his years in England, where he attended Cambridge University during World War I. The film follows his relationships with his mother Komalatammal, his wife Janaki, and his collaborator Professor G. H. Hardy. The film also showcases how Indian society viewed a mathematician of such great stature.[2]